  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): beta-10\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nno out-of-bounds check for negative array indices\r\n```python\r\nxs: uint256[10]\r\n\r\n@public\r\ndef bar() -> uint256:\r\n    return self.xs[-1]\r\n```\r\ngenerates this:\r\n```python\r\n          [eq, [mload, 0], '4273672062' <bar()>],\r\n          [seq,\r\n            [assert, [iszero, callvalue]],\r\n            # Line 5\r\n            [mstore, 0, [sload, [add, [sha3_32, '0' <self.xs>], [uclamplt, -1, 10]]]],\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nIf array index is `int128`, add `uclampge 0` for the index",
